description:
secretx-aws-sm/src/lib.rs:25 has 'use std::sync::Arc;'. Yet the inventory::submit! blocks at lines 254-269 use fully-qualified 'std::sync::Arc' four times (lines 258 twice, 266 twice).

The fully-qualified form is sometimes needed inside macros that expand into scopes where the local 'use' doesn't apply, but inventory::submit! is a declarative macro that expands at the call site — local imports are visible. Verify with a quick s/std::sync::Arc/Arc/ pass; if it compiles, ship it.

Fix:

    inventory::submit!(secretx_core::BackendRegistration {
        name: "aws-sm",
        factory: |uri: &str| {
            AwsSmBackend::from_uri(uri)
                .map(|b| Arc::new(b) as Arc<dyn secretx_core::SecretStore>)
        },
    });

If for some reason it does NOT compile (e.g. inventory uses a hygienic expansion that hides the use), then leave as-is and add a one-line comment noting the macro hygiene constraint. But verify before assuming.
